# Personal Portfolio Website

## Preview

<img width="100%" src="./assets/portfolio.png">

## Overview

This is my personal portfolio website, showcasing my skills, experiences, and projects as a front-end developer. The website is designed to provide an overview of my journey as a developer and to display my latest projects.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Demo](#demo)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Technologies](#technologies)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## Features

- Responsive design for various screen sizes and devices.
- Detailed sections for personal information, experiences, and projects.
- Interactive navigation menu for easy access to different sections.
- Smooth scrolling behavior for a seamless user experience.
- Stylish scrollbar customization for webkit-based browsers.
- Bio section with a brief overview of my journey and skills.
- Experience section with details of my work experiences and technologies used.
- Projects section showcasing my latest projects with descriptions and links.
- External links to my email and social media profiles.
- Readable and clean code with organized CSS styles.

## Demo

You can view a live demo of the website here: [Personal Portfolio Demo](https://guilhermesenci.github.io/portfolio/)

## Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine using `git clone https://github.com/guilhermesenci/portfolio.git`
2. Navigate to the project directory using `cd your-portfolio`

## Usage

To use this template for your own portfolio website:

1. Replace the content in the HTML file with your own information.
2. Customize the styles in the CSS file to match your design preferences.
3. Add your own project details and images to the HTML file.
4. Modify the navigation links to point to your website sections.
5. Update external links to your own profiles and contact information.

Feel free to adapt the template to your needs and make it unique to showcase your skills and projects.

## Technologies

This project uses the following technologies:

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

